Italy’s Confezioni Andrea to Open Serbian Plant, Novosti Reports

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-12-07T07:24:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/italy-s-confezioni-andrea-to-open-serbian-plant-novosti-reports.html
Confezioni Andrea Srl, an Italian
maker of covers for cars and motorcycles, will invest 9 million
euros ($12 million) to open a factory in Jagodina, central
 Serbia , Vecernje Novosti  reported , citing Deputy Premier Verica Kalanovic.  With Fiat’s local production seen as its key client, the
plant will employ 500 people and may receive government
incentive of 9,000 euros for each job created, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  